    to describe the public catalog data the demo was built on.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Accuracy of information</h2>
  <p>
    Prices, specifications, ratings, and availability come from a static catalog
    snapshot supplemented by third-party APIs, and the assistant's replies are generated
    by a large language model. <strong>Any of it may be outdated, incomplete, or plainly
    wrong.</strong> Don't base a real purchase decision on it without checking an actual
    retailer.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>
    Don't use the assistant to probe, overload, or disrupt the service, and don't submit
    anyone's real personal data — the booking form works just as well with fiction.
  </p>

  <h2>5. No warranty</h2>
